{"article_id":"9Fbpx1DANtAMBsdD","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"I ' ve never thought","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"the big Ford-Kavanaugh hearing","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"scheduled for Thursday","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"would actually happen .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"Maybe I ' ll be proved wrong ,","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"but I ' ve never believed","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"Christine Blasey Ford wants to testify .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"This hearing is not going to settle the issue of what , if anything , happened 36 years ago","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"- which ,","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"as I ' ve noted ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"is why there is no point","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"in having the hearing .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Senator Chuck Grassley , the Judiciary Committee chairman , should just invite affidavits from the witnesses","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"and call it a day .","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"Democrats , in any event , would rather have the specter of Ford ' s testimony than the real thing ,","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"given that the latter will highlight :","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"( a ) her inability","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"to recall and relate rudimentary details ,","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"( b ) the fact","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"that she did not utter a word about the alleged sexual assault for 30 years ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"( c ) the discrepancies between her current version of events and the notes of what she told her therapist ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"and ( d ) the fact","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"that the other witnesses","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"she has identified","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"do not corroborate her story .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"Moreover ,","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"now that Republicans have reportedly retained an experienced female litigator","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"to conduct the questioning ,","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"there is no longer the prospect of video clips","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"featuring Ford","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"being grilled by old white guys","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"- grist for what Democrats hoped would be their \" War on Women 2.0 \" campaign ads .","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"Ford ' s legal team continues to add new demands .","depth":6},{"id":33,"text":"The latest is a push","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"to have two \" trauma experts \" and Ford ' s polygrapher testify .","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"The purpose of these outlandish proposals is likely to prompt denials","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"that would allow Ford to bow out of the hearing ,","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"blaming purported GOP intransigence and insensitivity .","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"This underscores","depth":5},{"id":39,"text":"that the point of the hearing is being lost .","depth":5},{"id":40,"text":"A few days ago ,","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"when Democrats were demanding","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"that the FBI be dispatched to investigate Ford ' s nearly four-decade-old allegation ,","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"I pointed out :","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"Even though the FBI had jurisdiction","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"to conduct a background investigation of Kavanaugh ,","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"such investigations are not occasions to trigger full-blown criminal investigations of","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"[ alleged state ] crimes","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"the Justice Department has no jurisdiction","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"to prosecute ,","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"but rather result in a flagging of allegations for the Senate ' s consideration","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"( which has been done here ) .","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"The FBI inquiry into Judge Kavanaugh ' s background is not a criminal investigation .","depth":4},{"id":53,"text":"The hearings","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"attendant to the nomination","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"are not intended to be a trial .","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"Thursday ' s hearing ,","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"supplementing the 31 hours of testimony","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"Judge Kavanaugh has already provided ,","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"is not even ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"as he suggests ,","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"a forum","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"for \" clearing my name \"","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"- though he may understandably hope for that ,","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"just as one supposes","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"that Ford hopes for some measure of vindication .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"The proceedings are about Kavanaugh ' s suitability","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"to sit as an associate justice of the Supreme Court .","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"Period .","depth":6},{"id":69,"text":"The objective is to give the Senate","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"- first the Judiciary Committee and then the full chamber -","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"enough information","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"to make a discriminating appraisal of Kavanaugh ' s legal erudition and character .","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"On that score , the Senate has more information about this nominee","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"- including , most significantly , the 300 appellate opinions","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"he has authored on the eminent D.C . Circuit Court of Appeals -","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"than any nominee in the history of the United States .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"The Senate is not being asked to solve alleged crimes .","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"Its job is not to psychoanalyze witnesses .","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"Lawmakers , instead , are exercising their constitutional duty","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"to provide advice to the president on a nomination","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"and ,","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"if appropriate ,","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"to consent to a nominee ' s accession to office .","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"That ' s it .","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"Since Democrats are hell-bent on turning the ongoing Kangaroo Court into a pseudo-trial ,","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"it is worth noting how ridiculous that notion is .","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"To begin with , a trial requires jurors","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"who have been vetted for their objectivity .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"What we have here , instead , is a political theater","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"in which every Democrat is immovably predisposed to vote against the nominee","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"-","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"regardless of whether it is Kavanaugh or anyone else","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"President Trump appoints","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"to fill any Supreme Court vacancy .","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"All the banter about \" presumption of innocence \" is silly .","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"The proceeding is not about guilt or innocence ;","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"it is about qualification ,","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"and Democrats are presuming Kavanaugh ' s lack of qualification ,","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"no matter how overwhelming his résumé and how manifest his command of American jurisprudence .","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"But let ' s pretend","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"we were in a trial setting .","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"If that were so ,","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"the case would be thrown out of court .","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"First , Thursday ' s uncertain spectacle is scheduled","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"only because the confirmation process has been abused .","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"Democrats willfully sat on Ford ' s allegations","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"and raised them in an untimely manner after the hearing .","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"New meager allegations have come out of the woodwork in the same fashion .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"In a normal legal proceeding , these claims would be deemed waived by the failure","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"to raise them in a timely fashion","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"and submit them to the regular hearing process .","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"If Grassley agreed to have the record supplemented by written submissions from witnesses about these allegations ,","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"that would not only have been sufficient","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"but more than Democrats were entitled to under the circumstances .","depth":12},{"id":115,"text":"More to the point , no court would entertain these allegations .","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"The reason","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"the Constitution requires a speedy trial in criminal cases ,","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"and the reason","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"the law imposes statutes of limitations","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"( in federal law , it is usually five years ) ,","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"is that unreasonable delay unfairly prejudices an accused ' s right","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"to present a defense .","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"After five years , to say nothing of 36 years , physical evidence is no longer available ,","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"witnesses are often unavailable ,","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"and","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"even if witnesses can be produced ,","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"their memories have faded","depth":14},{"id":128,"text":"and become unreliable .","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"There is no way","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"to conduct a proceeding","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"that satisfies fundamental fairness .","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"Thus , the absurd irony :","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"Democrats want to ignore","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"that the proceeding here is merely an exploration of Kavanaugh ' s fitness","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"to be a judge","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"( which has been established beyond cavil ) ;","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"but while they want to turn the proceeding into a criminal trial ,","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"the case would be thrown out","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"if we were operating under trial standards .","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"The allegations are hopelessly stale ,","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"and the Judiciary Committee would be disqualified as fact-finder","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"because its members have already made up their minds about the outcome .","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"In the first 150 years of constitutional governance , nominees did not appear at confirmation hearings .","depth":7},{"id":144,"text":"After all , their public records were more than sufficient","depth":8},{"id":145,"text":"for lawmakers to appraise their suitability ,","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"and they could not ethically answer the questions of real interest","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"- how they would decide various kinds of cases .","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"It was better back then .","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"It was particularly better than what hearings became in the 1980s ,","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"when television and \" borking \" made them hyper-politicized","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"- theater","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"that was as much about celebrity senators as judicial nominees .","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"The Kavanaugh hearings have descended into farce .","depth":6},{"id":154,"text":"They are unfair by constitutional standards","depth":7},{"id":155,"text":"and unedifying by commonsense standards .","depth":7},{"id":156,"text":"I continue to doubt","depth":7},{"id":157,"text":"there will be a hearing on Thursday .","depth":7},{"id":158,"text":"I have no doubt","depth":8},{"id":159,"text":"that there should not be a hearing .","depth":8},{"id":160,"text":"There should be a vote .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":321,"left":200,"right":320,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":200,"left":174,"right":199,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS